The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, gave a briefing on various topics. He announced that President Obama would be making remarks about the recently concluded meeting with the P5-plus-1 dealing with Iran. He also discussed the President's schedule for the following day, including his trip to Copenhagen, Denmark, for the Chicago 2016 presentation to the International Olympic Committee. The briefing also touched on topics such as healthcare reform, the situation in Afghanistan, and the firing of Mark Lippert, the Chief of Staff for the National Security Council.